comments: Porzingis (BOS) avoids making illegal contact with Brunson (NYK) during Brunson's driving shot attempt.
Hartenstein's (NYK) arm lightly brushes Tatum's (BOS) shoulder as he launches into the air for the rebound, and the contact is marginal.
Tatum's (BOS) pass deflects off of Hartenstein's (NYK) knee and goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Boston.
Porzingis (BOS) firms up in Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal lower body contact occurs as Brunson defends around the screen.
Porzingis (BOS) turns toward the sideline and briefly comes together with Barrett (NYK). The contact off-ball is marginal.
Randle (NYK) legally contests Porzingis' (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Porzingis (BOS) legally contests Barrett's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) extends his arm toward the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Brown (BOS) as he secures the rebound.
Hartenstein (NYK) and Porzingis (BOS) engage and disengage in transition.
Barrett (NYK) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) establishes a screening position in Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players disengage after the pick.
Quickley (NYK) legally contests Porzingis' (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) aligns along Tatum's (BOS) path at the start of his drive, and the contact is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) reaches in for the ball and illegal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) right arm, which affects his control of the ball.
Porzingis (BOS) momentarily rests his hand on Hartenstein's (NYK) side as the two players engage during the loose ball and the contact is marginal.
Brown (BOS) establishes a screening position in Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Randle (NYK) moves alongside Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs prior to Tatum's pass.
Tatum (BOS) raises his off-arm slightly as he begins to gather the ball and marginal contact occurs with Randle (NYK) prior to the pass.
Tatum (BOS) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two legal steps before releasing his pass.
Hartenstein (NYK) moves laterally into Porzingis' (BOS) path and delivers body contact that affects Porzingis' SQBR.
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Holiday's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as Holiday backs into the pick.
White (BOS) legally contests Quickley's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) momentarily rests his hands on Hartenstein's (NYK) side and marginal contact occurs as Tatum releases away during the loose ball.
Holiday (BOS) makes more than marginal contact with Hartenstein's (NYK) arm during his shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) extends his arm forward and makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) head, affecting his SQBR at the start of his dribble in the backcourt.

Tatum (BOS) gathers the ball and establishes his right foot as his pivot foot. Brunson (NYK) legally dislodges this ball, which allows Tatum to legally lift his right foot and re-plant before regathering the ball.
Tatum (BOS) releases the inbounds pass within five seconds after receiving the ball from the official.
Randle (NYK) commits a take foul on Pritchard (BOS). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Holiday's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the screen.
Holiday (BOS) moves alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs at the start of Brunson's drive.
Holiday (BOS) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) and Hart (NYK) come together at the same spot on the floor as White (BOS) deflects the loose ball away, and the contact is incidental.
Quickley (NYK) extends his hands toward the loose ball as Tatum (BOS) goes to the ground and Quickley cleanly recovers it before losing his own balance and falling to the floor.
White (BOS) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
